{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7af5b03097c9a6395", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "45", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A short linear object of length <math><mi>b</mi></math> lies on the axis of a concave mirror of focal length <math><mi>f</mi></math> at a distance <math><mi>u</mi></math> from the pole. The length of the image will be.", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "XvGRS", "text": "<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>b</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "vlAo5", "text": "<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>b</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "KiRL2", "text": "<math><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>b</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "Zg7Bo", "text": "<math><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>b</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "The concave mirror formula is<br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> .... (i)<br /><br />Since, for a given concave mirror, focal length <math><mi>f</mi></math> is fixed, we partially differentiate Eq. (i) to get<br /><br /><math><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>u</mi></math> ...... (ii)<br /><br />Multiplying Equation. (i) by <math><mi>u</mi></math> , we get<br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> or <math><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> ..... (iii)<br /><br />Using Equation. (iii) in Equation. (ii), we get<br /><br /><math><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>u</mi></math><br /><br />Given <math><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>.</mo></math> Therefore<br /><br /><math><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>b</mi></math><br /><br />The negative sign shown that image is longitudinally inverted. The magnitude of the size of the image is<br /><br /><math><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>\u03b4</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61964c922db938c3ec5c87e8", "6160243a86b518ff2afd9379", "6160243ae896b71d7f0f03d9", "61bb820fc1f688a120dfda9f", "61964c9102fe1de035852896", "61e7bd71a2dd607688d6c01b", "61c08989e3eba41a9e71354b", "61602437a04b762ba7dfcb47", "61602438690b07c861db4cc9", "6160243b7384a30f11cacc9e", "629109ef0299d67104ca49d5", "629f3a9295d059d5cc4d982e", "629621243e04d5d8ca7b92bd", "629f390e4eb9140dc965900d", "64eb06dd3118f713ecfef1b0", "66d5853ba75f05ee8564f575", "67921d651d5b5072da5e9aae", "67fdff46378e1624ea7b6984", "680920293a10446a207fdecb"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}}